# Kotlin Android Rules

## Dependency Injection

```kotlin
// ✅ Interface + Impl + Hilt binding
interface ScreenCaptureProvider {
    suspend fun capture(): ScreenshotData?
}

class ScreenCaptureProviderImpl @Inject constructor() : ScreenCaptureProvider { ... }

// In AppModule
@Binds abstract fun bindScreenCapture(impl: ScreenCaptureProviderImpl): ScreenCaptureProvider
```

## Hidden API Reflection (v2)

```kotlin
// ✅ Must try-catch + fallback
fun capture(): Bitmap? = try {
    SurfaceControl::class.java
        .getMethod("screenshot", ...)
        .invoke(null, ...) as? Bitmap
} catch (e: Exception) {
    Log.w("amctl", "SurfaceControl.screenshot() failed, falling back", e)
    null // caller degrades to shell command or Accessibility
}
```

## MCP Tools

- Tool interfaces are stable (shared by v1/v2); only internal routing changes via ToolRouter
- Parameter validation happens in the tool layer, not in providers
- Errors returned as `CallToolResult(isError = true)` + `TextContent`
